<section xml:id="C15.S16">
<title>Products</title>          
<para xml:id="C15.S16.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C15.S16.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="15.16.1" mode="display" xml:id="C15.S16.E1">F\left({a,b\atop c-\frac{1}{2}};z\right)F\left({c-a,c-b\atop c+\frac{1}{2}};z \right)=\sum_{s=0}^{\infty}\frac{{\left(c\right)_{s}}}{{\left(c+\frac{1}{2} \right)_{s}}}A_{s}z^{s}, if |z|&lt;1,</Math> where <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C15.S16.p1.m1">A_{0}=1</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C15.S16.p1.m2">A_{s}</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C15.S16.p1.m3">s=1,2,\dots</Math> , are defined by the generating function <Math equation-number="15.16.2" mode="display" xml:id="C15.S16.E2">(1-z)^{a+b-c}F\left(2a,2b;2c-1;z\right)=\sum_{s=0}^{\infty}A_{s}z^{s}, if |z|&lt;1</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
  
<para xml:id="C15.S16.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C15.S16.p2.s1">
Also, <Math equation-number="15.16.3" mode="display" xml:id="C15.S16.E3">F\left({a,b\atop c};z\right)F\left({a,b\atop c};\zeta\right)=\sum_{s=0}^{ \infty}\frac{{\left(a\right)_{s}}{\left(b\right)_{s}}{\left(c-a\right)_{s}}{ \left(c-b\right)_{s}}}{{\left(c\right)_{s}}{\left(c\right)_{2s}}s!}\left(z \zeta\right)^{s}F\left({a+s,b+s\atop c+2s};z+\zeta-z\zeta\right), if |z|&lt;1, |\zeta|&lt;1, |z+\zeta-z\zeta|&lt;1</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C15.S16.p2.s2">
<Math equation-number="15.16.4" mode="display" xml:id="C15.S16.E4">F\left({a,b\atop c};z\right)F\left({-a,-b\atop-c};z\right)+\frac{ab(a-c)(b-c)} {c^{2}(1-c^{2})}z^{2}F\left({1+a,1+b\atop 2+c};z\right)F\left({1-a,1-b\atop 2- c};z\right)=1</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<paragraph xml:id="C15.S16.Px1">
<title>Generalized Legendre’s Relation</title>    
<para xml:id="C15.S16.Px1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C15.S16.Px1.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="15.16.5" mode="display" xml:id="C15.S16.E5">F\left({\frac{1}{2}+\lambda,-\frac{1}{2}-\nu\atop 1+\lambda+\mu};z\right)F \left({\frac{1}{2}-\lambda,\frac{1}{2}+\nu\atop 1+\nu+\mu};1-z\right)+F\left({ \frac{1}{2}+\lambda,\frac{1}{2}-\nu\atop 1+\lambda+\mu};z\right)F\left({-\frac {1}{2}-\lambda,\frac{1}{2}+\nu\atop 1+\nu+\mu};1-z\right)-F\left({\frac{1}{2}+ \lambda,\frac{1}{2}-\nu\atop 1+\lambda+\mu};z\right)F\left({\frac{1}{2}- \lambda,\frac{1}{2}+\nu\atop 1+\nu+\mu};1-z\right)=\frac{\Gamma\left(1+\lambda +\mu\right)\Gamma\left(1+\nu+\mu\right)}{\Gamma\left(\lambda+\mu+\nu+\frac{3}{ 2}\right)\Gamma\left(\frac{1}{2}+\nu\right)}, if |\operatorname{ph}z|&lt;\pi, |\operatorname{ph}\left(1-z\right)|&lt;\pi</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
  
<para xml:id="C15.S16.Px1.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C15.S16.Px1.p2.s1">
For further results of this kind, and also series of products of hypergeometric functions, see Erdélyi et al. (1953a, §2.5.2).
</sentence>

</para>
 
